svg.desc: The chart shows the proportion of persons with at least secondary school (II) graduation by age group and gender in 2016. In that year, a total of 87 percent of those aged 25-64 had completed a university entrance qualification or vocational training. The figure for women stood at 85 percent and for men at 88 percent. Women were however demonstrating increasing success in education. Women aged 25-34 have completely caught up with their male counterparts. √çn 2017, the share of men with at least secondary school (II) graduation was slightly below and that of women slightly higher than 87 percent.

div.p:
Source: German Federal Statistical Office, Results of the 2016 Microcensus.
